HEADWORD: Litherly
<hw>Li"ther*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Crafty; cunning; mischievous;
wicked; treacherous; lazy.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [the dwarf] was waspish, arch, and <qex>litherly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithesome</ent>⟦br⟧
